FMNR promotes the growth of trees, which has multiple benefits. Rinaudo (2012) notes that FMNR:

                           •

produces firewood and building timber;


                           •

contributes to restoration;


                           •

positively impacts crop yields and animal production;


                           •

increases biodiversity and reduces dependence on pesticides;


                           •

contributes to the local economy; and


                           •

contributes to the quality of life.
